    "markdown": "---\ntitle: Create tracks\nexecute:\n  freeze: auto\n  echo: true\n---\n\n\n\n\n## Introduction\n\nObjectives:\n\n- Create minimum convex polygons for individual caribou\n- Calculate movement rates\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nlibrary(sf)\nlibrary(amt)\nlibrary(tidyverse)\n```\n:::\n\n\n\n\n### Read locations and convert to simple features (sf object)\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\ngps <- read.csv('../data/yt/gps.csv') |>\n  mutate(timestamp=as.POSIXct(timestamp),\n    id = ID, x=longitude, y=latitude)\nglimpse(gps)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\nRows: 90,864\nColumns: 8\n$ timestamp <dttm> 2020-11-06 19:10:39, 2020-11-07 01:07:00, 2020-11-07 07:05:…\n$ longitude <dbl> -129.2876, -129.3327, -129.3022, -129.3021, -129.3146, -129.…\n$ latitude  <dbl> 60.24530, 60.19127, 60.17469, 60.17254, 60.14960, 60.14822, …\n$ ID        <int> 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 4316…\n$ season    <chr> \"earlywinter\", \"earlywinter\", \"earlywinter\", \"earlywinter\", …\n$ id        <int> 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 4316…\n$ x         <dbl> -129.2876, -129.3327, -129.3022, -129.3021, -129.3146, -129.…\n$ y         <dbl> 60.24530, 60.19127, 60.17469, 60.17254, 60.14960, 60.14822, …\n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n### Make tracks\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\ncaribou <- sf::st_read('../data/yt_caribou.gpkg', 'gps')\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\nReading layer `gps' from data source \n  `C:\\Users\\PIVER37\\Documents\\little_rancheria\\data\\yt_caribou.gpkg' \n  using driver `GPKG'\nSimple feature collection with 90864 features and 3 fields\nGeometry type: POINT\nDimension:     XY\nBounding box:  xmin: 518681.7 ymin: 480918.5 xmax: 716666.7 ymax: 651698.2\nProjected CRS: NAD83 / Yukon Albers\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nglimpse(caribou)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\nRows: 90,864\nColumns: 4\n$ timestamp <chr> \"2020-11-06 19:10:39\", \"2020-11-07 01:07:00\", \"2020-11-07 07…\n$ ID        <int> 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 43163, 4316…\n$ season    <chr> \"earlywinter\", \"earlywinter\", \"earlywinter\", \"earlywinter\", …\n$ geom      <POINT [m]> POINT (678102.7 642940.6), POINT (675905.1 636811.4), …\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\ncaribou <- mutate(caribou, x_=st_coordinates(caribou)[,1],\n    y_=st_coordinates(caribou)[,2],\n    t_=ymd_hms(timestamp),\n    id=paste0('C',ID),\n    name='Caribou',\n    timestamp=NULL, ID=NULL) |>\n    st_drop_geometry()\nglimpse(caribou)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\nRows: 90,864\nColumns: 6\n$ season <chr> \"earlywinter\", \"earlywinter\", \"earlywinter\", \"earlywinter\", \"ea…\n$ x_     <dbl> 678102.7, 675905.1, 677688.9, 677707.0, 677144.5, 675848.0, 676…\n$ y_     <dbl> 642940.6, 636811.4, 635054.2, 634815.6, 632232.1, 632013.4, 632…\n$ t_     <dttm> 2020-11-06 19:10:39, 2020-11-07 01:07:00, 2020-11-07 07:05:54,…\n$ id     <chr> \"C43163\", \"C43163\", \"C43163\", \"C43163\", \"C43163\", \"C43163\", \"C4…\n$ name   <chr> \"Caribou\", \"Caribou\", \"Caribou\", \"Caribou\", \"Caribou\", \"Caribou…\n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n### Make tracks\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\ntr <- make_track(caribou, x_, y_, t_, name = id, crs = 3578)\nprint(summarize_sampling_rate_many(tr, cols='name'), n=25)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n# A tibble: 25 × 10\n   name     min    q1 median  mean    q3    max     sd     n unit \n * <chr>  <dbl> <dbl>  <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>  <dbl>  <dbl> <int> <chr>\n 1 C43161 0.474  5.98   5.98  7.14  5.99 1173.  27.9    1759 hour \n 2 C43147 5.94   5.98   5.98  6.01  5.98   12.0  0.389  2126 hour \n 3 C43146 5.94   5.98   5.98  6.01  5.98   29.9  0.505  4898 hour \n 4 C43144 5.94   5.98   5.98  6.00  5.98   12.0  0.283  4908 hour \n 5 C43159 5.94   5.98   5.98  6.00  5.98   12.0  0.351  4904 hour \n 6 C43141 5.94   5.98   5.98  6.0